# Shell scripts MUST keep LF line endings. They are COPYed into Linux
# containers and run as the image ENTRYPOINT (see tutor-platform-api/Dockerfile).
# If the repo is delivered via `git clone` on a Windows machine with the default
# core.autocrlf=true, these files would be rewritten to CRLF and the kernel
# would fail to exec the `#!/bin/sh` shebang ("no such file or directory").
# Pinning eol=lf here makes every delivery method (git clone or zip) safe.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Same reasoning for the entrypoint regardless of extension.
docker-entrypoint.sh text eol=lf
